problem:
A box of mass $m_1$ initially moving at speed $v_1$ collides perfectly inelastically with a box of mass $m_2$ moving at speed $v_2$ (i.e. they stick).
    \begin{anum}
        \item If one box initially moves in the negative $x$-direction and the other moves in the positive $x$-direction, find their final speed. 
        \item If one box initially moves in the $y$-direction and the other moves in the $x$-direction, find their final speed.
    \end{anum}

solution:
\begin{anum}
        \item Let box 1 move in the positive direction and box 2 move in the negative direction. If the boxes stick together, they have the same final velocity $v$ after the collision. By conservation of momentum, $$m_1v_1-m_2v_2=(m_1+m_2)v\Rightarrow v=\boxed{\frac{m_1v_1-m_2v_2}{m_1+m_2}}$$
        \item If the boxes move perpendicularly, the total momentum will be found by adding their vectors via the Pythagorean theorem: $$p=\sqrt{p_x^2+p_y^2}=\sqrt{(m_1v_1)^2+(m_2v_2)^2}$$Again, since the boxes stick together, they have the same velocity after the collision. So, $$v=\frac{p}{m_1+m_2}=\boxed{\frac{\sqrt{(m_1v_1)^2+(m_2v_2)^2}}{m_1+m_2}}$$
    \end{anum}

problem:
A pool ball with initial speed $v$ is aimed right between two other pool balls as shown. If the two right balls leave the (elastic) collision with equal speeds, find the final velocities of all three balls.
    \begin{center}
        \includegraphics[scale=0.2]{pool}
    \end{center}

solution:
Since the impulse to the two right balls comes from the normal force, their final velocities must be directed in the direction of the normal force at the moment of contact. Thus, the two right balls scatter each at an angle $30^\circ$ to the horizontal. Let their speeds be $w$ and the speed of the left ball to be $u$ after the collision (let the rightward direction be positive). By conservation of momentum in the $x$-direction, $$mv=mu+2mw\cos(30^\circ)$$and by conservation of energy, $$\frac 12 mv^2=\frac12 mu^2+2\cdot\frac12mw^2$$Solving the system yields \begin{gather*}
        u=\boxed{-\frac 15 v}\\
        w=\boxed{\frac{2\sqrt 3}{5}v}
    \end{gather*}

